          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(14,165,233,0.1);color:#0ea5e9">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M9 11l3 3L22 4"/><path d="M21 12v7a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h11"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">Devine Formula</h3>
          <p class="info-text">The most widely used formula in clinical settings. Originally developed in 1974 for drug dosing calculations. Men: 50 + 2.3 kg per inch over 5 ft. Women: 45.5 + 2.3 kg per inch over 5 ft.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(16,185,129,0.1);color:#10b981">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M22 11.08V12a10 10 0 1 1-5.93-9.14"/><polyline points="22 4 12 14.01 9 11.01"/></svg>
          </div>
          <h3 class="info-title">Robinson Formula</h3>
          <p class="info-text">Developed in 1983, slightly more generous than Devine. Men: 52 + 1.9 kg per inch over 5 ft. Women: 49 + 1.7 kg per inch over 5 ft.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <div class="info-icon" style="background:rgba(249,115,22,0.1);color:#f97316">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/></svg>
