          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Ideal body weight is an estimated weight considered healthiest for a given height, determined using medical formulas like Devine, Robinson, Miller, and Hamwi. These formulas calculate based on height and gender, originally developed for clinical pharmacology.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">Which ideal weight formula is most accurate?<svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>No single formula is definitively most accurate. The Devine formula is most common in clinical use. Using the average of all four provides the most balanced estimate.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">Does frame size affect ideal weight?<svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. People with larger skeletal frames naturally weigh more. A small frame may reduce ideal weight by 10%, while a large frame may increase it by 10%. Use the wrist measurement method to estimate your frame size.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">What is the ideal weight for 5 feet 8 inches?<svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>For a male at 5'8" (173 cm), the ideal weight is approximately 63–72 kg (139–159 lbs). For a female, approximately 59–68 kg (130–150 lbs). Frame size can shift these values by ±10%.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)" aria-expanded="false">Is ideal weight the same as healthy weight?<svg class="faq-arrow" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"/></svg></button>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Not exactly. Ideal weight is a formula-derived single point, while healthy weight is a range (BMI 18.5–24.9). You can be at a healthy weight without being at your calculated ideal weight.</p></div>
        </div>
